article.description: — Julien Wooden's 23 points helped James Madison defeat Old Dominion 78-62 on Wednesday night.

article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- — Julien Wooden's 23 points helped James Madison defeat Old Dominion 78-62 on Wednesday night. Wooden had five rebounds for the Dukes (18-2, 7-2 Sun Belt Conference). Noah Freidel scored 15 points while going 4 of 10 from the floor, including 3 for 7 from 3-point range, and 4 for 4 from the line, and added nine rebounds and five assists. T.J. Bickerstaff shot 5 of 10 from the field and 2 for 5 from the line to finish with 12 points. The Monarchs (5-15, 1-8) were led by Vasean Allette, who posted 15 points, six rebounds and five assists. Old Dominion also got 14 points from Tyrone Williams. In addition, Chaunce Jenkins had 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
